    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Magnitude of SARS-CoV-2 virus exposure may contribute to symptom severity. In a sample of seropositive adults (n=1101), we found that individuals who lived with a known COVID-19 case exhibited greater symptom severity and IgG concentrations compared to individuals who were seropositive but did not live with a known case (P&lt;0.0001).</jats:p>",
